cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with automated natural language processing and information extraction from transcripts of interviews with domain experts. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of different models for capturing context dependency, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on the application of cognitive task analysis, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with the limited and noisy nature of the labeled data, which is a common issue in information retrieval (cs.IR).
